<br>
A good technique I have seen so far is a &quot;circle of death&quot; aggro kite, kinda thing.<br>
<br>
I get aggro with snare and fire/debuff/makemad dot, kite it in circles, with pup nipping at heals, while i re-cast to get aggro back when pup takes aggro, and Shaman does the DoT thing while medding alot.<br>
<br>
Any other tips from the field?<br>
<br>
Thanks. <p><B><a href = "mailto:irontree_ravenstrike@yahoo.com">Irontree Ravenstrike (Druid 34)</a></B><BR><BR>
Ravensign (11 Ranger)
Utterance (16 SK)




</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unorpin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Norpin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/5/01 2:01:48 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duoing with Shaman Advice</span><hr size=1> I'm surprised the pet can get aggro.  Is the shaman remembering to turn off pet taunt? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubrairwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Brairwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/5/01 5:47:59 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duoing with Shaman Advice</span><hr size=1> Have the shaman do the blind spell, like a level 5 spell.  Acts like a fear so dots do full damage.  Pup does not get smacked when you do that either. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utoktukwartalon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Toktuk Wartalon</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/8/01 1:19:37 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duoing with Shaman Advice</span><hr size=1> Instead of kiting, you could have the Shaman pull the mob with Malise and pull back to a location to keep it rooted. Just drop your DoTs on it and let the mob slowly die. Re-root when needed. If you want, the Shaman could slow and you both could do a little melee with pet. Just make sure to keep Chloro/Regen and AC/HP buffs up and you should do fine.<br>
<br>
-Tok <p>__________________<br>
<div style="font-size: 9pt; font-family: Verdana;"><b><a href="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=97559" target="_blank">Toktuk Wartalon</a></b></div>
<div style="font-size: 8pt; font-family: Verdana;">Proud Shaman of War<br>
Clan Bloodtalon, Tunare<br>
<br>
<i>Mine is the fist of death!</i></div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwannawin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wannawin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/8/01 3:43:17 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://animation.acmecity.com/stopmo/273/pictures/shortclip07.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duoing with Shaman Advice</span><hr size=1> root / DoT works best and slow and then let pet hit, at least, at level 56 and 57 it works that way :)<br>
<br>
I partner often with shaman, rocks, cause almost never stacking issues :) <p>Wannawin Litlewolf, an animal loving druid <BR>
Walaf Weaponmaster, the mighty short pirate <BR>
"HAR HAR, Shiver me timbers!"
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uoramaathon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>OramaAthon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/8/01 9:19:15 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duoing with Shaman Advice</span><hr size=1> Just to chime in ----<br>
<br>
Root/Dot is definately the best method.  Once the shaman get plauge mobs drop really quick.<br>
<br>
A warning however.  Despite the fact that the shaman has a better dot (and should be rooting), the mob will be aggro'ing you if root breaks b/c (snare, dot's (immolate and swarm series), and maybe RFS).<br>
<br>
Let the shaman nuke if necessary to get aggro, b/c they can just recoup mana w/ cannibalize (+cholor = wow!).<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uborashaman.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BoraShaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/8/01 12:53:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duoing with Shaman Advice</span><hr size=1> The whole kiting pet strategy is very weak.  You have to stay up and running around the whole time and your not really aiding the shaman at all, at least no to the best of your abilities.  <br>
<br>
Better to work on the shaman strenghs slow/pet.  Put a DS on the pet and do the regen/heal while the shaman does haste/slow.  Each drop a dot but mostly conserve mana and med while pet fights. Root if necessary to keep mob on pet.<br>
If the pet has trouble tanking then let the shaman tank.  A good shaman should have sufficiently high AC to tank a slowed mob at most levels.<br>
<br>
I'd say this strat would be good for 39+ I dont recall seeing your level.  I think root/dot is a great tactic also if somewhat boring.<br>
<br>
This is from the perspective of a level 57 shaman.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uwannawin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wannawin</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/10/01 3:32:31 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.cartoonnetwork.com/home/img/favorites.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duoing with Shaman Advice</span><hr size=1> -----quote--<br>
