</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ujezabelbatsmasher.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jezabel Batsmasher</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_magentaspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(10/15/01 2:51:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duoing with Shaman Advice</span><hr size=1> My hubby is Shaman. Been parterning with him since level 29 (In high 50's now). We are good enough where we did the basement of Kanors to get the VP key peice with just us two. Course being in the same room in RL where you can talk helps a lot too :).<br>
<br>
Depends on situation who pulls (how far of a pull, can we keep the pet in line, danger of pet pathing, do we have full control of the area and spawn times yet, who needs mana). If he pulls, he does so with Slow, if I pull I do with Epic (snare), and he is sure to cast slow as I come running in. He immediatly puts the pet on it and the pet takes the agro for a shortime, long enough for him to get his dots off (including epic - helps a lot when both have epics). Shaman then will usuually chain Canabalize, or do his bracer a time or two depending - He use to chain bracer, I beleive he has changed that and canabliezes more now during the battle - we seem to be able to keep moving faster that way. He usually tanks by that point due to the agro of his dots, and bracer blasts. I do my best not to get too high on agro so I can sit while my dots work, don't always work out that way tho, as you said snare is agro, epic and WD pretty high agro, I am usually not agroed upon until I sit down.  <br>
<br>
If he pulls I'll wait a tad before throwing epic in so I can med. Then just blast it more towards the end. If I pulled with epic, I can give up the idea of sitting down so I go ahead and put in WD and bonk it or blast.<br>
<br>
We don't usually root except for the adds. Thoes we park them and cook them away (at least with epics) while we are active on the original pull. <br>
<br>
Also whoever pulls stops at a distance so if there are multiples gives the other a chance to root one before pulling in. That way we start out with the un-wanted add rooted at a distance, and also agroed on the 2nd person, not all agroed on the poor puller. We have done HS entrance, pit and now Chardok using this method. Anyplace where there is enough room to root/park mobs.<br>
<br>
OH yeah, Keep thorns on whoever seems to be agro as well :). Sure wish group thorns did the pet.<br>
 <p><font size=5><font color=pink>Jeza</font> </font><br>
Grrrr. Bark. Bark. Grrrr. <br>
